HEADWORD: Pehlevi
<hw>Peh"le*vi`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Parsee
<ets>Pahlavi</ets>.]</ety> <def>An ancient Persian dialect in which
words were partly represented by their Semitic equivalents. It was in
use from the 3d century (and perhaps earlier) to the middle of the 7th
century, and later in religious writings.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Pahlavi</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

